Kiess has no formal presence in the Great Northern Forest — it lies between Midgaard and Kowloon, east of Kiess's position on Roc Road. Trade Syndics receive Lantern Road status reports from Midgaard road warden channels, treating forest conditions as a factor in eastern trade timing. The forest's joint-commission governance model — neither city claims sole authority, disputes go to neutral witness judgment — is viewed positively by Kiess as institutional design preventing either city from using road control as political leverage. By contrast, Roc Road's dual-authority problem lacks the forest road's clean neutral-ground framework, which Kiess convoy marshals cite as persistent jurisdictional friction.

