Mafdet's interest in the Great Northern Forest is as the northern end of the overland trade chain that Mafdet's harbor receives at its southern end. Lantern Road status affects the timing and reliability of Kowloon-origin and forest-harvest cargo reaching Midgaard, which affects eastern desert routes and ultimately Mafdet's harbor intake scheduling. Forest-origin commodities — processed timber, medicinal bark, bog iron, mire-clan trade goods — arrive at Mafdet attested through Midgaard manifest seals. Mafdet has no institutional knowledge of or presence in the forest; its relationship is entirely downstream.

