Rivennid ecological understanding identifies the Great Northern Forest as a partially intact ancient root-network ecosystem under sustained human pressure. The Verdant Depths at the northern heart are the oldest and most ecologically coherent zone. The Everkeepers' planting-rings were the only human infrastructure compatible with the root network's autonomous cycles. The Lantern Road, built using the Bent Mile Principle, is also ecologically compatible — it yields to terrain rather than cutting through ecologically significant zones. Rivennid in Midgaard track the Thornwood substrate crystal formation as an existential concern: the failing binding is already affecting root-network behavior in the estate-forest's margins, and if the crystal substrate fully destabilizes, the effect on nearby root network segments is not predictable from any current ecological model.

